oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Brown, L.N.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Pasture conditions
Protein
Pregnancy Palpation
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: When the supply of available food dwindles for a given animal population, there is often a resulting decrease in fertility and reproductivity. The veterinarian often observes similar principles at work in the cow-calf herd.
